bibl.title: P. Mich. inv. 33: A Fragment of a Martyrology?
bibl.note: P. Mich. Inv. 33 [ed.: James L. McMILLAN, Fragment of a Martyrology, StPap 16 (1977) pp. 69-72] is the end of a parchment codex which probably contained the Passion of Saint Dioscorus. It teaches us that the praefectus Aegypti Clodius Culcianus did not leave his office earlier than 18 December 307.
